<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="276" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,798,1795]" pageId="6" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1734,1759]" pageId="6" pageNumber="276">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[865,971,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="276">fusoideus</emphasis>
, referring to the fusiform sclerite of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
